{"id": 231222018, "title": "Beloved dad fatally shot in the neck after trying to break up argument near his home", "text": "A loving father was gunned down by a homeless man after trying to break up an argument outside his home Nicolas Gandara, 38, was fatally shot in his neck while trying to quell an argument right outside his home in Monrovia, California, on June 2. The suspect named Christopher Wiggan, 42, fled the scene but was later arrested the following afternoon when he returned to the same spot. Nicolas was the sole provider for the family and worked two jobs as a social media manager and truck driver. READ MORE: Woman, 71, mauled to death by black bear who raided home before rangers track and kill animal He is survived by his wife, Darlene Sarti and their six children- Nicolas, Dominic, Sebastian, Jordan, Mya, and their six-week old daughter Mariah. Darlene confirmed that the murder suspect lived steps away in a homeless encampment that had been problematic. While talking to Eyewitness News, she spoke about her husband who she says \"went above and beyond\" for his family. \"He was a great guy. My kids miss him so much, and I can see the pain in their eyes. He was an amazing dad, an amazing provider. \"He went above and beyond to make sure that we were good,\" she added. The family welcomes their sixth child, a girl two months ago, and the couple have been married for 14 years. READ MORE: Nyima Ward dead at 27 as tributes paid to son of 90s supermodel Trish Goff Darlene said: \"We were so good that it broke up something so perfect, and it was taken by someone who doesn't care about anything, and he came and destroyed everything we worked so hard for.\" Christopher faced one charge of murder and an additional allegation of personally using a firearm in the commission of the crime, confirmed by Los Angeles County District Attorney George Gasc\u00f3n. Despite pleading not guilty during his arraignment, he could potentially face life imprisonment if convicted. He is scheduled for a preliminary hearing setting conference on June 20 at Dept. H of the Los Angeles County Superior Court, Pasadena Branch, the defendant was remanded into custody without bail. Click here to follow the Mirror UK on Google News to stay up to date with all the latest news, sports and entertainment stories \"I\u2019m deeply saddened by the tragic loss of an innocent husband and father of six, who was senselessly shot and killed outside his own home,\" District Attorney Gasc\u00f3n said. \"I extend my deepest condolences to the victim\u2019s family and assure you that we are here to support you in any way that we can. Such heinous acts of violence have no place in our society and will not be tolerated. We are committed to seeking justice for the victim and his family and will work tirelessly to ensure that the individual responsible for this heinous crime is held accountable.\" The Los Angeles County Sheriff\u2019s Department is investigating the case. A GoFundMe has been created by his sister, Dali Gandara, and has raised $71,000 since his demise. The post reads: \"His life was cut short as he was a victim of a senseless crime that we cannot digest. The LAPD are continuing their efforts to bring justice for this act. \"Nic was truly the most vibrant, optimistic, ambitious person who loved his family more than anything in the world. Anyone that knew my brother knows that his presence was larger than life. \"He would go out of his way to advocate for his friends and family members. He had an uncanny ability to somehow make everyone in his large circle feel loved and special. He truly was above and beyond and this tragedy has left the giant hole in our hearts.\"", "summary": "The family of the dad-of-six has been left devastated after he was tragically shot dead as he tried to break up an argument outside his home in Monrovia, California", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/us-news/beloved-dad-fatally-shot-neck-32988241", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article32988142.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/3_dad-3JPG.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 12:42:12", "author": "Rashi Agarwal,Rashi-Agarwal", "authors": ["Rashi Agarwal", "Rashi-Agarwal"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.2}